<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-4210] Zookeeper c client: detect connection loss during opportunistic async send</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-4210</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When an async operation is performed in the C client, the client will attempt to send the command to the server if this would not block.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When this send reports an error (eg: EPIPE) this is reported up to the async message, but the return code is not stored and checked, making it impossible for the user of the c client library to identify this case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can eventually trigger an assertion in some IO libraries, eg libev, because the file descriptor libev is watching is not associated with a valid stream.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Observed on Linux 3.x 4.x 5.x Centos distributions.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
